<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-01T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="1029" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1029">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6354/167: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-01T17:00:00+01:00">November
                                    1, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 1—12:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2238. I had an opportunity of seeing Malcolm MacDonald last night and
                            having a talk with him about the tin situation and his office telephoned
                            today to say that the Dutch had withdrawn their objection to the British
                            proposal and that therefore the Chairman’s communiqué had been issued
                            raising the tin quota for the current quota [<hi rend="italic">quarter</hi>] to 100% and for the first quarter of 1940 to not less
                            than 60%. Please inform Commerce of quota changes.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>